# AWS 2-Tier Architecture Diagram

## Architecture Flow

                Internet Users
                       |
                       v
            Application Load Balancer
                       |
        -------------------------------
        |                             |
        v                             v
  App Server 1 (Private AZ-a)   App Server 2 (Private AZ-b)
        |                             |
        --------------------------------
                       |
                       v
                Database Layer
                  (RDS / DB)

---

## Network Architecture

VPC (10.0.0.0/16)

Public Subnets:
- 10.0.1.0/24 (AZ-a)
- 10.0.2.0/24 (AZ-b)

Private Subnets:
- 10.0.3.0/24 (AZ-a)
- 10.0.4.0/24 (AZ-b)

---

## Components

1. Internet Gateway  
   Allows internet access to public resources

2. NAT Gateway  
   Allows private instances to access internet securely

3. Bastion Host  
   Used to SSH into private EC2 instances

4. Application Load Balancer  
   Distributes traffic across multiple EC2 instances

5. Auto Scaling Group  
   Automatically increases/decreases instances

6. CloudWatch  
   Monitors system performance

7. SNS  
   Sends alerts via email

---

## Request Flow

User → ALB → Auto Scaling Group → EC2 Instances (Private Subnet)

Admin Access:

User → Bastion Host → Private EC2

---

## High Availability

- Multi Availability Zone deployment
- Load balancing across instances
- Auto scaling ensures uptime during high load

---

## Security

- Private subnets for application servers
- Bastion host for secure SSH access
- Security groups restrict traffic
